content.description:
Goblout climbs from the south end of the tunnel, through 12ft of coarse but bomber hand/fist jams, and tops out with pure willpower on the north end.

Start with at least one hand jammed on the outermost part of the tunnel, the other is up to you.
content.protection: Despite being 4ft off the ground, I recommend a pad. Sometimes the foot jams can be a bit too bomber, and more people than I expected have pinwheeled out going headfirst towards the ground.
content.location: Located on the south side of the main Woodson trail, between the Ogre and Yoav cracks. ~10mins from the summit.
